# Methodological & architecture decisions — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Durable decisions for this project: methodology, experimental design choices,
infrastructure architecture. This file is project memory — it answers "why is it
done this way?" for future sessions and collaborators.

Rules:

- Append new entries below the marker, newest first.
- Log only significant decisions. Trivial choices do not belong here.
- Never log secrets, credentials, or sensitive/embargoed data.
- A decision is **proposed** by Claude and recorded only after the researcher
  accepts it (`reference/human-in-the-loop-policy.md`).
- When a decision is replaced, mark the old entry `Status: superseded by …`
  instead of deleting it.

Entry format:

```markdown
## <YYYY-MM-DD> — <short decision title>

- Status: active            # active | superseded | rejected
- Context: <why a decision was needed — what result, failure, or constraint prompted it>
- Decision: <what was decided>
- Alternatives rejected: <what lost; details may go to rejected-options.md>
- Consequences: <what this commits the project to>
- Revisit if: <conditions that would reopen the question, or "unlikely">
- Source: <card ID / analysis report / notebook entry that settled it>
```

